Quote: <i>Collar:</i> The narrow steel clamp on the drifter-drill column placed below the horizontal arm to provide temporary support while the arm was being loosened off to shift the drill to a new position or when `lining up' on a hole.
Notes: Glossary of Waihi Mining Terms
